# Build-context excludes for the showcase gateway image (build context = repo root,
# because the Dockerfile copies templates/<id>/{src,backend}). Keeps the context
# small and avoids `archive/tar: write too long` from live/huge dirs.
#
# Only the templates' src/ + backend/ and showcase/gateway are needed; everything
# heavy or volatile is excluded. The templates have their OWN Dockerfiles with
# their own (template-dir) contexts, so this does not affect them.

# Volatile / generated
**/.venv
**/node_modules
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache

# VCS / tooling
.git
.github
**/.azure
**/.env
**/.env.local
*.log

# Frontends + build output (the gateway image never needs these)
templates/*/frontend
templates/*/hosted
showcase/ui
**/dist
**/.next

# Docs / session noise
**/*.md
